    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-04T14:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-04T14:36:00-05:00" n="1102"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1102">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/359.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-04T13:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1912—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Embassy is constantly receiving urgent appeals from American citizens who, on
                    account of the widespread disturbances and business depression, have lost all
                    their property through no fault of their own. In many cases they are unable to
                    remain longer in the interior. Are there any funds, Red Cross or other, which
                    could be <pb facs="0925" n="809" xml:id="pg_809"/> placed at the disposal of the
                    Embassy to be used with the greatest discretion and only after thorough
                    investigation of each case for temporary relief of such persons and for
                    returning them to the United States?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
